'''Naila Al Moosawi''' is an Emirati business executive who has been a pioneer woman in the Middle East.
In 1998 she became an [[air traffic controller]] at [[Dubai International Airport]], making her the first woman air traffic controller in the Middle East. Resigning that job after having children, in 2001 she became the first female site manager at the [[Emirates National Oil Company]].<ref>[http://www.gulfindustryworldwide.com/news/813_First-woman-site-manager-at-Enoc.html First woman site manager at Enoc], ''Gulf Industry'', Vol. 10, Issue 2 (March-April 2001).</ref>
Today she is a Director at [[LafargeHolcim]].<ref>[http://micequotient.com/awilb4#SpeakersArab Women in Leadership and Business Summit – 4th Edition: Speakers]</ref>
