{{BLP sources|date=August 2016}} '''Shalva Chigirinsky''' is a Jewish [[Russians|Russian]] businessman operating in real estate and oil sectors.
==Early life and education== Shalva Chigirinsky was born in 1950 in [[Kutaisi]]. He graduated from the [[Moscow Medical Academy]].<ref name=forbes/>
==Career== In 1987, he emigrated to Spain and later to Germany, where in 1989, he became a co-founder of the real estate development company STT Group.<ref name=forbes/> In 1990s in became a major shareholder of [[Sibir Energy]], a London-listed Russian oil company. In 2009, the company sued Chigirinsky for at least US$325&nbsp;million for a failed bid to sell his real estate assets to the company.<ref name=reuters080709> {{cite news | url= http://uk.reuters.com/article/idUKLH70922520090717?sp=true | title= Moscow eyes bigger Sibir stake amid shareholder probe | author = Katya Golubkova | publisher=[[Reuters]] | date=2009-07-17 | accessdate=2009-09-13}} </ref> He faces several other lawsuits in different jurisdictions.<ref name=reuters240809> {{cite news | url= http://uk.reuters.com/article/oilRpt/idUKB43369920090824 | title= Russia's VTB says wins lawsuit against Chigirinsky | author = Dmitry Sergeev | publisher=[[Reuters]] | date=2009-08-24 | accessdate=2009-09-13}} </ref> His stake in the company was taken over by [[Sberbank]], pledged as loan collateral.<ref name=reuters240809b> {{cite news | url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/idUKLO50423520090824 | title = Sibir Energy secures $200 mln loan from Sberbank | author = Dmitry Sergeev | publisher=[[Reuters]] | date=2009-08-24 | accessdate=2009-09-13}} </ref> There is an investigation concerning alleged tax evasion by Chigirinsky.<ref name=reuters080709/>
==Personal life== Chigirinsky is divorced and has six children.<ref name=forbes> {{cite news | url= https://www.forbes.com/lists/2008/10/billionaires08_Shalva-Chigirinsky_1KH0.html | title= Shalva Chigirinsky | publisher=[[Forbes]] | date=2008-03-05 | accessdate=2009-09-13}} </ref> He and the mother of four of his children, Tatiana Panchenkova, divorced in 2009. She testified in a Connecticut court that he beat her for more than ten years.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2274470/Shalva-Chigirinsky-Russian-oligarch-brutally-beat-ex-wife-caused-suffer-miscarriage-decade-abuse.html | location=London | work=Daily Mail | title=Russian oligarch's ex-wife tells Connecticut court he 'brutally beat her for more than a decade and caused her to suffer a miscarriage'}}</ref>
